nd Musco for \$p = {\textbackslash}infty\$. Further, we prove a matrix-vector query lower bound of \${\textbackslash}Omega(1/{\textbackslash}epsilon\^{}\{1/3\})\$ for any fixed constant \$p {\textbackslash}geq 1\$, showing that surprisingly \${\textbackslash}tilde\{{\textbackslash}Theta\}(1/{\textbackslash}epsilon\^{}\{1/3\})\$ is the optimal complexity for constant{\textasciitilde}\$k\$. To obtain our results, we introduce several new techniques, including optimizing over multiple Krylov subspaces simultaneously, and pinching inequalities for partitioned operators. Our lower bound for \$p {\textbackslash}in [1,2]\$ uses the Araki-Lieb-Thirring trace inequality, whereas for \$p{$>$}2\$, we appeal to a norm-compression inequality for aligned partitioned operators.},
